<h2>EV-Specific Installation Considerations</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Camera &amp; Sensor Areas:</strong> Tesla Autopilot cameras, radar units, and ultrasonic sensors are carefully masked and avoided during installation. We never cover functional sensors.</li>
<li><strong>Charge Port Door:</strong> The charge port door is wrapped as a separate panel to ensure clean lines and easy access. We use precision-cut templates for each EV model.</li>
<li><strong>Frunk (Front Trunk):</strong> The frunk lid is wrapped separately with special attention to the unique geometry of each EV model.</li>
<li><strong>Aluminum Panels:</strong> Rivian and other EVs with aluminum body panels require special surface preparation to ensure proper vinyl adhesion without risk of galvanic corrosion.</li>
<li><strong>Glass Roof Panels:</strong> Tesla&rsquo;s panoramic glass roof can be wrapped with tinted vinyl for heat reduction and privacy, using automotive-grade window film.</li>
<li><strong>Paint Compatibility:</strong> Tesla&rsquo;s water-based paint is fully compatible with cast vinyl wraps. We perform a paint hardness test on all vehicles before installation.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Frequently Asked Questions About EV Wraps</h2>
<div class="ev-faq">
<details>
<summary>Will wrapping my Tesla void the warranty?</summary>
<div class="faq-body">No. Vinyl wraps do not void Tesla&rsquo;s vehicle warranty. Tesla&rsquo;s warranty covers manufacturing defects in materials and workmanship, not cosmetic modifications. Wrapping is a reversible cosmetic modification that does not affect mechanical or electrical systems. However, we recommend consulting your specific warranty documentation. When professionally installed and removed, wraps leave no damage to the original paint.</div>
</details>
<details>
<summary>Can I wrap a Rivian R1T or R1S?</summary>
<div class="faq-body">Yes, absolutely. We have extensive experience wrapping Rivian R1T trucks and R1S SUVs. Rivian&rsquo;s aluminum body panels require special surface preparation, which our team is trained to perform. We have wrapped Rivians in solid color changes, camo patterns, holographic finishes, and branded fleet wraps (including Blue Origin delivery vehicles). See our gallery above for examples.</div>
</details>
<details>
<summary>How do I wash my wrapped EV?</summary>
<div class="faq-body">Hand washing is recommended for wrapped vehicles. If using a car wash, avoid high-pressure washes directed at wrap edges, and avoid brush-type automatic car washes. Touchless car washes are generally safe. For Tesla owners with the built-in car wash mode, it is safe to use with a wrapped vehicle as long as the wrap edges are properly sealed. We provide detailed care instructions with every wrap installation.</div>
</details>
<details>
<summary>Can I wrap just the roof or hood of my Tesla?</summary>
<div class="faq-body">Yes. Partial wraps are a popular and cost-effective option. Common partial wrap configurations for EVs include: roof wrap only (matte black or carbon fiber), hood wrap, roof + hood combination, mirror caps, door handle accents, and rocker panel wraps. Partial wraps start from $800 depending on the panels selected.</div>
</details>
<details>
<summary>How long does an EV wrap installation take?</summary>
<div class="faq-body">A full color change wrap on a Tesla Model 3 or Model Y typically takes 2&ndash;3 business days. Larger vehicles like the Tesla Model X or Rivian R1S may take 3&ndash;4 days. Partial wraps can often be completed in 1 day. We offer free fleet pickup and delivery throughout Chicagoland so your EV can be wrapped without disrupting your schedule.</div>
</details>
<details>
<summary>Does wrapping protect my EV&rsquo;s paint?</summary>
<div class="faq-body">Yes. Vinyl wraps provide a physical barrier against minor scratches, stone chips, UV fading, and environmental contaminants. This is particularly valuable for EVs, which often have higher resale values than comparable ICE vehicles. A well-maintained wrap can be removed after 5&ndash;7 years to reveal factory-fresh paint underneath, potentially increasing resale value. For maximum paint protection, we also offer PPF (Paint Protection Film) hybrid installations.</div>
</details>
</div>

